questions.question:
A senior engineer writes the following Python patch block to handle three versions of a payment processing step:

```python
if patched('v2'):
    process_payment_v2()
elif patched('v3'):
    process_payment_v3()
else:
    process_payment_v1()
```

They deploy this to production. New Workflow Executions that have never been seen before start running. Which code path will they follow?
